``` ::: ::: ### Tidy the data First we need to remove the duplicate columns from each of the data set ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} cattle_diary_new <- subset(cattle_dairy,select= -c(`Year Code`)) ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} head(cattle_diary_new) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A tibble: 6 × 13 Domain …¹ Domain Area …² Area Eleme…³ Element Item …⁴ Item Year Unit Value 1 QL Lives… 2 Afgh… 5318 Milk A… 882 Milk… 1961 Head 7 e5 2 QL Lives… 2 Afgh… 5420 Yield 882 Milk… 1961 hg/An 5 e3 3 QL Lives… 2 Afgh… 5510 Produc… 882 Milk… 1961 tonn… 3.5e5 4 QL Lives… 2 Afgh… 5318 Milk A… 882 Milk… 1962 Head 7 e5 5 QL Lives… 2 Afgh… 5420 Yield 882 Milk… 1962 hg/An 5 e3 6 QL Lives… 2 Afgh… 5510 Produc… 882 Milk… 1962 tonn… 3.5e5 # … with 2 more variables: Flag , `Flag Description` , and # abbreviated variable names ¹​`Domain Code`, ²​`Area Code`, ³​`Element Code`, # ⁴​`Item Code` ``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} livestock_new <- subset(livestock,select= -c(`Year Code`)) egg_new <- subset(egg_chicken,select= -c(`Year Code`)) ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} cattle_diary_new<- cattle_diary_new%>% mutate(Item=str_replace_all(Item,"Milk, whole fresh cow", "Milk")) egg_new <- egg_new%>% mutate(Item=str_replace_all(Item,"Eggs, hen, in shell","Poultry")) table(cattle_diary_mutate$Item) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-error} ``` Error in table(cattle_diary_mutate$Item): object 'cattle_diary_mutate' not found ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} table(egg_new$Item) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Poultry 38170 ``` ::: ::: Now that we have renamed the columns, now we perform a join on the tidied data. ## Join Data we have same columns in cattle, diary and live stock tables. so when we join them the final data must have the rows summated together in all the tables. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} cattle_egg <- full_join(egg_new,cattle_diary_new) joined_data <- full_join(cattle_egg,livestock_new) ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} dim(joined_data) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] 156735 13 ``` ::: ::: we now confirm that they are all joined together. ## Visualizations ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} ggplot(joined_data,aes(x=Item))+geom_bar(fill = "lightpink") + labs(title = "Item and count", x = "Item", y = "Count")+geom_text(stat='count', aes(label=..count..), vjust=1) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](Tejaswini_Ketineni_challenge8_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-27-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: Now, we have understood that we can perform visualizations too on joined data.
